rules.name: Public types, methods and fields (API) should be documented with Javadoc
Exception handlers should preserve the original exceptions
Standard outputs should not be used directly to log anything
Exit methods should not be called
Unused method parameters should be removed
Generic exceptions should never be thrown
Classes and methods that rely on the default system encoding should not be used
Utility classes should not have public constructors
Return values from functions without side effects should not be ignored
Null pointers should not be dereferenced
Unused local variables should be removed
Magic numbers should not be used
Bad practice - Method ignores exceptional return value
Style - Unused public or protected field
Class variable fields should not have public accessibility
Local variable and method parameter names should comply with a naming convention
Boolean literals should not be redundant
"Serializable" classes should have a version id
Fields in a "Serializable" class should either be transient or serializable
